{"nodes":[{"id":"366ca6aa-571e-4a81-bd37-2c210f7e8e8a","x":2313,"y":-1625,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Modern Centralized Core Architecture in Scala\n\n**CQRS **- Scala/Akka has wonderful framework built-in\ncausality principles (action/reaction), FSM in-memory State accessible in real-time**Actors** (entities) distributed in shards of nodes in a **cluster**Each actor is being sourced relevant transactions\nbuilding its **account** balance in-memory (fast-access)Each Transaction is used for building general projections\n**Projections** are part of the design\n\n![Screenshot from 2023-10-25 23-13-49](https://orgpad.info/img/BRK2A1Bz1CE5Gw-FTEFF5r?token=Am33SedLBDCKgcsyIjbJZ9)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"0f0aaf63-19c9-408c-bcf2-4fc91235a347","x":4878,"y":-1645,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Centralized problems\n\n**Settlement layer**complex nightmare causing magic finality of Visa Payment Tx (reaching consensus) might take up to 3 days, the payment Fee is ~ 2%new parties or banks cannot easily join the centralized system or clusterinconsistency\nwe rely on database ACID capabilities, write thorough tests with fingers crossed (no cryptographical proofs)A lot of State to keep = **bad for Functional Programming****privacy**","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"936ef5d3-7c67-469c-b4c8-606c3ec3c687","x":4867,"y":660,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Blockchain Explorer decentralization\n\nindexes data and exposes http-api / graphQLoften provides also analytical insights **Centralized**making **projections** into powerful DBhard to incentivize people to run it**Decentralized**  : [The Graph](https://thegraph.com/)introduced incentivization model inversion of control, let index those who need it**subgraphs** of only parts of the chain that are relevant to themIndexing blockchain challenges\nhandling forks, rollbacks / reverting datavarious transaction formats and assetspartition size in Cassandra, JOINs in RDBM","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"953e0708-7bb4-46e1-a32b-9996743bcfdb","x":2304,"y":645,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Blockchain Standards\n\nGlobal, open set of standards reminds of democracy.\n\n![mathematics-11-00101-g001](https://orgpad.info/img/DfKvJdHqFE-oAOZwCg4wP-?token=BubsQoLGdPR6WkN8hD5NOy)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"dc5427bd-a651-4b85-adbc-d20fdad28552","x":-128,"y":-234,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Asset Custody - Bridge between centralized and decentralized world\n\nRobust multi-client wallet backed by DBclassic cryptography : PGP, BouncyCastle[https://github.com/pragmaxim/zio-pass](https://github.com/pragmaxim/scalapass-cli)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"5a5b2993-2adb-4af5-a7b8-551a2d761599","x":1078,"y":-1605,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Centralized Banking\n\n**WW II** (Bretton Woods system): 3 decades of regulation, fixed exchange and interest rates worldwide provided some financial stability\n\n**1970s - 2008** : deregulation => massive techno-feudalism and inflation as we know it today\n\n1970s : Nixon shock, floating exchange rates, end of gold standard1980s : rise of derivatives, junk bonds, etc.1990s : rise of securitization, subprime mortgages, etc.\n\n**2008+ **: printing money\n\namount of transactions increasing exponentially since Web2.0","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"6b21ceaa-2795-4cb0-b0e5-9ce78e4bcbda","x":4876,"y":-2656,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Unbalanced Data Distribution\n\nPostgresSQL : custom DB optimizations / paginationCassandra : hash/time/range partitioning + denormalizationusing Cloud Storages for $ : BigTable / BigQuery\n\n![Screenshot from 2023-10-28 12-03-09](https://orgpad.info/img/CH3Wy-gTxOhLs2tUn3nDRm?token=B_9tMhsiNCS5JNcu9o1Lt_)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"0f83d398-c2f6-4d1a-9015-bbce1a887b44","x":3635,"y":-1665,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## CQRS (Command-Query-Responsibility-Segregation)\n\n![cqrs-es-flowwhite](https://orgpad.info/img/AfncXNB0RJd5xDoShHGkME?token=BETqFmezNP6acJfL-BKDI6)\n\nideal use-case for distributed Actor System\ncentralized on a single clusterakka persistence + queryeach actor represents an Account/Entity (in-memory State)you are **NOT** forced to message driven architectureZio Entity (discontinued)\ninspired by Lagom and Aecor (both discontinued)EventSourced, EventStore ...\ndiscontinued or not used much","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"d8f90dfd-e2a6-4489-8f1f-a8936a2d942d","x":3604,"y":-428,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Relay & Para Chains\n\nHow sustainability is done? Through further decentralization.\n\n![polygon-architecture](https://orgpad.info/img/BudYBNN-RJ95w2E9WeYNqP?token=B6oKNd2QBCLpI6gml8N8_C)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"7068432d-5216-4809-a2fc-23dc342a9bd2","x":-101,"y":-2630,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Centralized vs Decentralized\n\n![bank](https://orgpad.info/img/DEZfr1wVJOaqmG6MoNSFzT?token=CrqTfm80pP4LsEUwg9A8PA)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"053f25f3-6cc0-4226-aaa1-6262448a949a","x":1062,"y":674,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Decentralized Apps\n\n![Applications-of-Smart-Contract-31-Finance-Smart-contracts-can-potentially-reduce](https://orgpad.info/img/A66XfemdNAfoRSWm6SpFPB?token=CA7fww_EJO35GI9i43SUxC)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"53035eb0-81df-4711-9db6-e65cbfa215ac","x":4863,"y":-448,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Advantages of decentralization\n\nClean standards of **Settlement/Consensus layer**in **peer-2-peer** network\n any party can join**good for Functional Programming** as only State to keep is Mempool of Txs and Peers Fast finality - time required to reach consensus\n[Solana](https://solana.com/)/[Avalanche](https://www.avax.network/)consistency - provably correct datastructures\n[Merkle tree database](https://github.com/ava-labs/firewood/) privacy\nusers own the data[ZK proofs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zero-knowledge_proof), [Ring signatures](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring_signature)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"ba50c269-ced7-4447-a09b-3fba20bb7846","x":-118,"y":-1938,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Paradigm shift through analogy\n\nWhat software reminds me of\n\n**Centralized**  - totalitarian state and centrally controlled economy**Decentralized** - democratic state and free economy (slightly utopian)**Hybrid**  - realistic balance and sustainability","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"22d33959-323f-4fbe-910e-3541324a5452","x":-127,"y":-1058,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Shared traits of Centralized & Decentralized worlds\n\n**Settlement** between all involved parties\nall parties need to reach **concensus** about **State****finality** = time required to reach consensus**throughput** = how many txs/s**Event Sourcing** - causality based, replayable sequence of **action & reaction** => quickly accessable State **Transaction Log** => **Account Balances****Transaction** is mostly a container of asset transfers between accounts\n**Asset** = Fiat, anything of value, ownership**Account** represents a balance, a container of assets**Projections** of Transation Log to get better insights\n\n","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"deb3fcb2-4ff0-45be-8e38-ca8c85b50318","x":1059,"y":-419,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Decentralized Banking\n\n**Satoshi Nakamoto**\n\nacademia + many years of working in Fintechdemocratized and open-sourced bankinginspired by decentralized file sharing\n\n**2. generation of blockchains**\n\nself-governance : DAOgeneral-purpose, rich smart-contractssustainability issues and bottlenecks\n\n**3. generation of blockchains**\n\nhigh throughput, low finality : Solana, Avalanche\nmerkle-tree DB replacement of RocksDBRelay-chain & Para-chain combination \nsustainability ","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"b781c423-c217-4aba-9e6b-6e184b2dceb8","x":3592,"y":636,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Crypto proofs for fast consensus\n\nMerkelized Trie Database : [Firebase](https://github.com/ava-labs/firewood/)Patricia Merkle Trie on RocksDB : [Trie-db](https://github.com/paritytech/trie)Authenticated Dynamic Dictionaries : [AVL+ tree](https://github.com/ergoplatform/ergo/tree/master/avldb)\n\n![YZGxe](https://orgpad.info/img/DCIvFcYHRF1I8BjKZ9oD1M?token=A_-FVvZqRJeo4NxWwXpghZ)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"53c2197f-5c7d-4608-af3f-c1759b7d9f58","x":2325,"y":-414,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Decentralized Core Architecture in Scala\n\n**peer-2-peer** network and stateless Node are ideal for [ZIO](https://zio.dev/)Blockchain and Projections are **separated**Blockchain = TxLedger + AccountState ([zio-chain](https://github.com/pragmaxim/zio-chain))Projections = **Blockchain Explorer** ([uexplorer](https://github.com/pragmaxim/ergo-uexplorer))TxLedger + AccountState are **provably correct** and consisent with each other and accross whole p2p network![Screenshot from 2023-10-25 23-14-08](https://orgpad.info/img/BLQ0c5EVNAI7xKdhuP7ktG?token=AEc0Aev_RAOpa8iMLUUaob)\n\n","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"b42dfbba-7dd1-47c5-9e9b-6df2cb98e6f0","x":3634,"y":-2737,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Unbalanced Cluster Distribution\n\n![big-data-complexity-visual-representation-cluster-analysis-visualization-advanced-analytics-beauty-graphic-abstract-background-196869505-transformed](https://orgpad.info/img/Bhs-MjjgZOEamQCU3neoZj?token=DtzalgVa9NsIPIsNeRlRZF)\n\n**Problem**\n\n\n\nNodes can have different concentration of Whales and Sharks\npay-for-service transactionsday trading \n\n⇒ performance issues, bottlenecks, replay time varies, etc.\n\n**Solution**\n\nrank-based cluster rebalancing","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"2a8fe17b-0c37-465e-b3d3-61903e46ee2b","x":1102,"y":-2592,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## CEFI\n\n![SWIFT +Connecting+the+Global+Financial+Community](https://orgpad.info/img/D0tTlK0CRBSIyVzQAoP9kZ?token=A7hzhh3FNN65x9k_FXZ9X3)","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"8320d0cc-6244-45da-bd76-c2d852d18f30","x":2327,"y":-2579,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Centralized Standards\n\nMany specifications showed up over time\n**ISO20022** - unified messaging format**FIX** - real-time messaging format**FpML** - describes financtial products **CBPR+** - framework for enhancing cross-border payments developed by CPMI and IOSCO**ISDA **- International Swaps and Derivatives Association**PCI DSS** - security standards designed to ensure that all companies that accept, process, store, or transmit credit card information maintain a secure environment\n\n","color":"#2f7ba7"},{"id":"d1397c24-d2ec-4a21-b8fd-ba6164d3ebfb","x":-220,"y":654,"width":50,"height":50,"type":"text","text":"## Jakub Liška  @ Pragmaxim\n\n![px-logo-flapless-narrow-blur-shadow-1280](https://orgpad.info/img/A_IskaKzpFf4LjUG-mxZvE?token=BYGMPgQx9FI6vqyRtmCd9d)\n\n![px-logo-tear-narrow-blur-shadow-1280](https://orgpad.info/img/B4fLUaIw1KGrw2UaMCtQoz?token=AJBlZBW1NK2YPx5cw8ElRx)\n\nSpecialization on\n\ndistributed data processingblockchains\n\nusing mainly\n\n[Scala](https://www.scala-lang.org/) ecosystem[ZIO](https://zio.dev/)[Akka](https://akka.io/) based implementations of CQRS\n\nIdeally sustainable, green, meaningful or complexity reducing software that makes the world a better place.\n\nScala, Akka & ZIO help me to be useful and solve problems which is an opportunity to become even more useful and solve problems better by :\n\ndeeper understanding of some domain like Fintech and transaction processing softwareexploring new domains as people evolve this way and learn to look at the world differently ","color":"#2f7ba7"}],"edges":[{"id":"b4c97596-942f-400f-9992-9b91a89b9fc8","fromNode":"5a5b2993-2adb-4af5-a7b8-551a2d761599","fromSide":"top","toNode":"2a8fe17b-0c37-465e-b3d3-61903e46ee2b","toSide":"bottom","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"6fae5830-02d2-4d88-a907-b347d5ac3dbe","fromNode":"22d33959-323f-4fbe-910e-3541324a5452","fromSide":"right","toNode":"5a5b2993-2adb-4af5-a7b8-551a2d761599","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"249c4776-2edf-4784-b20d-58fe90f98bed","fromNode":"d8f90dfd-e2a6-4489-8f1f-a8936a2d942d","fromSide":"bottom","toNode":"b781c423-c217-4aba-9e6b-6e184b2dceb8","toSide":"top","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"b1f2da7b-3989-40cd-9d0d-6d36ba6f7da2","fromNode":"366ca6aa-571e-4a81-bd37-2c210f7e8e8a","fromSide":"right","toNode":"0f83d398-c2f6-4d1a-9015-bbce1a887b44","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"b7ced7a7-b977-405c-901f-7bc2bced9edb","fromNode":"0f0aaf63-19c9-408c-bcf2-4fc91235a347","fromSide":"top","toNode":"6b21ceaa-2795-4cb0-b0e5-9ce78e4bcbda","toSide":"bottom","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"771e436a-3776-4298-b32d-62cc506dff79","fromNode":"2a8fe17b-0c37-465e-b3d3-61903e46ee2b","fromSide":"right","toNode":"8320d0cc-6244-45da-bd76-c2d852d18f30","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"e6ecc440-2457-41f5-a57b-1de186f75613","fromNode":"053f25f3-6cc0-4226-aaa1-6262448a949a","fromSide":"right","toNode":"953e0708-7bb4-46e1-a32b-9996743bcfdb","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"fda0cce2-7f9e-4add-8b7c-fe647a654b71","fromNode":"d8f90dfd-e2a6-4489-8f1f-a8936a2d942d","fromSide":"right","toNode":"936ef5d3-7c67-469c-b4c8-606c3ec3c687","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"f120c084-97c1-4a09-830b-f59ce32f6afa","fromNode":"d8f90dfd-e2a6-4489-8f1f-a8936a2d942d","fromSide":"right","toNode":"53035eb0-81df-4711-9db6-e65cbfa215ac","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"f484ff37-67e5-4212-ae4f-71dc292ca2f2","fromNode":"53c2197f-5c7d-4608-af3f-c1759b7d9f58","fromSide":"right","toNode":"d8f90dfd-e2a6-4489-8f1f-a8936a2d942d","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"291823ac-bbd9-48c4-bbad-e3c097f37384","fromNode":"0f83d398-c2f6-4d1a-9015-bbce1a887b44","fromSide":"right","toNode":"0f0aaf63-19c9-408c-bcf2-4fc91235a347","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"b1623164-f2a5-47a5-8a77-7eed31b8fc43","fromNode":"5a5b2993-2adb-4af5-a7b8-551a2d761599","fromSide":"right","toNode":"366ca6aa-571e-4a81-bd37-2c210f7e8e8a","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"6c957adf-9774-401d-b4d3-b7fe766ef9b3","fromNode":"deb3fcb2-4ff0-45be-8e38-ca8c85b50318","fromSide":"right","toNode":"53c2197f-5c7d-4608-af3f-c1759b7d9f58","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"2e6cd8eb-bd97-472c-8d08-812303b2ab36","fromNode":"22d33959-323f-4fbe-910e-3541324a5452","fromSide":"right","toNode":"deb3fcb2-4ff0-45be-8e38-ca8c85b50318","toSide":"left","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"0f50dcdf-bb4d-41db-8bb8-e49629fbc681","fromNode":"22d33959-323f-4fbe-910e-3541324a5452","fromSide":"bottom","toNode":"dc5427bd-a651-4b85-adbc-d20fdad28552","toSide":"top","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"1dcd24a7-a58e-450e-8b75-9b3f191cd161","fromNode":"ba50c269-ced7-4447-a09b-3fba20bb7846","fromSide":"top","toNode":"7068432d-5216-4809-a2fc-23dc342a9bd2","toSide":"bottom","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"a9e98122-9c67-47bb-8af4-3c9e41b3e91f","fromNode":"0f83d398-c2f6-4d1a-9015-bbce1a887b44","fromSide":"top","toNode":"b42dfbba-7dd1-47c5-9e9b-6df2cb98e6f0","toSide":"bottom","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"9beda489-a673-48a5-8e33-e4f0122679e1","fromNode":"22d33959-323f-4fbe-910e-3541324a5452","fromSide":"top","toNode":"ba50c269-ced7-4447-a09b-3fba20bb7846","toSide":"bottom","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"},{"id":"dc3a37d2-37ab-412f-a374-03b8d905903a","fromNode":"deb3fcb2-4ff0-45be-8e38-ca8c85b50318","fromSide":"bottom","toNode":"053f25f3-6cc0-4226-aaa1-6262448a949a","toSide":"top","color":"#399ad3","toEnd":"arrow"}]}